# Buhi Supply Co — Cursor Rules
# Drop this file in the root of your Next.js project.
# Claude will read this at the start of every session to stay consistent.

## PROJECT IDENTITY

This is the Buhi Supply Co e-commerce website.
Brand: lifestyle bag brand targeting millennial female professionals and students.
Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.
Goal: production-ready, SEO-optimized, mobile-first e-commerce site.

---

## TECH STACK

- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router (`src/app/`)
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS with custom design tokens (see below)
- Fonts: Google Fonts via `next/font/google` — Open Sans (headings), Average Sans (body)
- Icons: `lucide-react`
- Images: `next/image` for all images (never plain `<img>` tags)
- Analytics: Google Tag Manager + GA4, Meta Pixel, TikTok Pixel

---

## FOLDER STRUCTURE

Always follow this structure. Do not deviate.

```
src/
  app/
    layout.tsx          # Root layout: fonts, GTM, Header, Footer
    page.tsx            # Homepage — composes section components
    globals.css         # Tailwind directives + CSS variables only
    (routes)/           # All other pages as route folders
  components/
    layout/
      Header.tsx        # Sticky nav
      Footer.tsx        # Site footer
    sections/           # Full-width homepage sections (one file per section)
      Hero.tsx
      LifestyleCategories.tsx
      Bestsellers.tsx
      TrustBar.tsx
      Testimonials.tsx
      EmailCapture.tsx
      UGCFeed.tsx
    ui/                 # Reusable atomic components
      ProductCard.tsx
      Button.tsx
      StarRating.tsx
      Badge.tsx
      SectionHeader.tsx
  lib/
    analytics.ts        # trackEvent() wrapper for GA4/Meta/TikTok
    types.ts            # Shared TypeScript interfaces (Product, Category, etc.)
  styles/
    tokens.ts           # Design token constants (mirrors tailwind.config.ts)
public/
  images/               # All static images
    hero.jpg
    lifestyle/          # Work, School, Travel, Gym category images
    products/           # Product images
    ugc/                # UGC grid images
```

---

## DESIGN TOKENS

These are the exact values from the Figma design. Use ONLY these values.
They are configured in `tailwind.config.ts` as custom theme extensions.

### Colors

| Token            | Hex       | Tailwind Class        | Usage                          |
|------------------|-----------|-----------------------|--------------------------------|
| primary          | `#3D4A3D` | `bg-primary`          | Main buttons, header CTA, nav  |
| accent           | `#264252` | `bg-accent`           | Subscribe button, highlights   |
| secondary        | `#3C422A` | `bg-secondary`        | Secondary actions              |
| muted            | `#585C62` | `text-muted`          | Body text, descriptions        |
| surface          | `#F0F2E9` | `bg-surface`          | Section backgrounds (Bestsellers, UGC) |
| background       | `#FFFFFF` | `bg-background`       | Default page background        |

Never use hardcoded hex values in components. Always use Tailwind token classes.

### Typography

| Element        | Font         | Weight | Size (desktop) | Tailwind                          |
|----------------|--------------|--------|----------------|-----------------------------------|
| H1 / Hero      | Open Sans    | Bold   | 60px           | `font-heading font-bold text-6xl` |
| H2 / Section   | Open Sans    | Bold   | 48px           | `font-heading font-bold text-5xl` |
| H3 / Card      | Open Sans    | Bold   | 20px           | `font-heading font-bold text-xl`  |
| Body / Subtext | Average Sans | Regular| 18px           | `font-body text-lg`               |
| Small / Label  | Average Sans | Regular| 14px           | `font-body text-sm`               |
| Price          | Open Sans    | Bold   | 24px           | `font-heading font-bold text-2xl` |
| Nav Links      | Average Sans | Regular| 16px           | `font-body text-base`             |

Letter spacing: always apply `tracking-tight` (`-0.5px`) to all text.

### Spacing

Use the 8px spacing scale. Always use Tailwind spacing utilities (`p-2` = 8px, `p-4` = 16px, `p-6` = 24px, `p-8` = 32px, etc.). Never use arbitrary pixel values unless there is no Tailwind equivalent.

### Borders & Radius

- Cards: `rounded-lg` (8px)
- Buttons: `rounded-md` (6px)
- Avatars/Circles: `rounded-full`
- Wishlist button: `rounded-full` with shadow

### Shadows

- Cards: `shadow-sm` (`0px 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.05)`)
- Wishlist button: `shadow-md` (`0px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)`)

---

## COMPONENT PATTERNS

### Buttons

Two variants only:

```tsx
// Primary (filled)
<button className="bg-primary text-white font-body text-base rounded-md h-[60px] px-8 tracking-tight hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
  Shop Bestsellers
</button>

// Secondary (outlined / white fill)
<button className="bg-white text-primary font-body text-base rounded-md h-[60px] px-8 tracking-tight border border-primary/20 hover:bg-surface transition-colors">
  Find Your Buhi Quiz
</button>

// Mobile CTA height
h-[48px]  // use on mobile, 48px minimum tap target
```

### Product Card

Always follow this exact structure:
- White card, `rounded-lg shadow-sm overflow-hidden`
- Image container: fixed 320px height on desktop, `object-cover`
- Wishlist button: top-right absolute, `rounded-full bg-white shadow-md`
- Optional badge (Trending/New): top-left absolute, small text label
- Content padding: `p-6`
- Name: `font-heading font-bold text-xl text-primary tracking-tight`
- Description: `font-body text-sm text-muted tracking-tight`
- Price: `font-heading font-bold text-2xl text-primary tracking-tight`
- Star rating: inline next to review count
- Add to Cart button: full-width, `bg-primary text-white h-12 rounded-md`

### Section Headers

Reuse `<SectionHeader>` component:
```tsx
<SectionHeader
  title="Bestsellers"
  subtitle="Our most-loved bags for every lifestyle"
/>
```
Always centered. Title in `font-heading font-bold text-5xl text-primary`, subtitle in `font-body text-lg text-muted`. 96px top/bottom section padding.

### Section Backgrounds

Alternate between these two backgrounds section by section:
- White: `bg-background` (Hero, Lifestyle, Testimonials)
- Sage: `bg-surface` (Bestsellers, UGC)
- Dark: `bg-primary text-white` (Email Capture, Footer)

---

## LAYOUT RULES

### Header (Desktop)
- Height: 80px, sticky, `bg-white border-b border-gray-200 z-50`
- Logo: left, 32px from edge
- Nav: horizontally centered
- Right side: search icon → cart icon (with badge) → "Shop Bestsellers" button
- Nav links: `font-body text-base text-muted tracking-tight`

### Header (Mobile)
- Height: 72px
- Hamburger: left
- Logo: centered
- Cart + search: right
- "Shop Bestsellers" button moves into the hamburger menu

### Footer
- Background: `bg-primary text-white`
- Layout: 4 columns desktop (Brand | Shop | Support | Company)
- Brand column: Logo + "Bags built for your everyday adventures" + social icons (Instagram, TikTok, Facebook)
- Footer bottom bar: copyright left, Google Analytics logo right
- Mobile: stacked accordion

---

## RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS

Always write mobile-first CSS. Use these breakpoints:

| Breakpoint | Min Width | Usage                    |
|------------|-----------|--------------------------|
| (default)  | 0px       | Mobile (375px base)      |
| `sm`       | 640px     | Large mobile             |
| `md`       | 768px     | Tablet                   |
| `lg`       | 1024px    | Desktop                  |
| `xl`       | 1280px    | Wide desktop             |
| `2xl`      | 1440px    | Full design width        |

### Mobile-Specific Rules

- Hero: stack text above image, `text-4xl` heading, full-height 600px
- Product grid: 2 columns (`grid-cols-2`)
- Lifestyle categories: 2×2 grid
- Navigation: hamburger menu
- Buttons in hero: stack vertically, full-width
- Email capture: input and button stack vertically
- Footer: accordion-style, no columns
- UGC grid: horizontal scroll (`overflow-x-auto flex gap-4`)

---

## IMAGE RULES

- Always use `next/image` with `alt` text
- Hero image: `fill` layout with `object-cover`, `priority` prop
- Product images: `width={384} height={384}` on desktop
- Lifestyle category images: `fill` with `object-cover`
- UGC images: square aspect ratio, `object-cover`
- Add `loading="lazy"` to all non-hero images (next/image handles this by default)

---

## ANALYTICS RULES

All user interactions must fire through `trackEvent()` from `src/lib/analytics.ts`.

Events to track:
```ts
trackEvent('product_view', { product_id, name, price })
trackEvent('add_to_cart', { product_id, name, price })
trackEvent('email_signup', { source: 'homepage_footer' })
trackEvent('quiz_start')
trackEvent('lifestyle_category_click', { category })
```

`trackEvent` fires to:
1. `window.gtag` (GA4 via GTM)
2. `window.fbq` (Meta Pixel)
3. `window.ttq` (TikTok Pixel)

Never call `window.gtag` / `window.fbq` / `window.ttq` directly in components — always go through `trackEvent`.

---

## TYPESCRIPT RULES

Always define shared types in `src/lib/types.ts`. Key interfaces:

```ts
interface Product {
  id: string
  name: string
  description: string
  price: number
  rating: number
  reviewCount: number
  image: string
  badge?: 'Trending' | 'New' | 'Bestseller'
  category: 'work' | 'school' | 'travel' | 'gym'
}

interface LifestyleCategory {
  id: string
  name: string
  description: string
  image: string
  href: string
}

interface Testimonial {
  id: string
  name: string
  title: string
  quote: string
  avatar: string
  rating: number
}
```

---

## SEO RULES

Every page must export a `generateMetadata()` function or static `metadata` object from `src/app/[page]/page.tsx`.

Homepage metadata:
```ts
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: 'Buhi Supply Co — Bags That Move With Your Life',
  description: 'Versatile, durable lifestyle bags for work, school, travel, and gym. Shop backpacks, totes, duffels, and more.',
  openGraph: { ... }
}
```

- All images must have `alt` text
- Use semantic HTML: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`, `<h1>`–`<h3>`
- Only one `<h1>` per page (the Hero headline)
- Section headings use `<h2>`, card titles use `<h3>`

