## FIGMA REFERENCE

The Figma design file is the source of truth for all visual decisions.
Key node IDs for reference in Cursor:

| Section                | Node ID  |
|------------------------|----------|
| Full Desktop Homepage  | `5:331`  |
| Full Mobile Homepage   | `7:396`  |
| Header (Desktop)       | `5:340`  |
| Hero Section           | `5:334`  |
| Shop by Lifestyle      | `5:335`  |
| Bestsellers Grid       | `5:336`  |
| Testimonials           | `5:337`  |
| Email Capture          | `5:1345` |
| #BuhiEverywhere        | `5:339`  |
| Footer                 | `5:1246` |
| Mobile Header          | `7:406`  |
| Mobile Hero            | `7:398`  |
| Mobile Bestsellers     | `7:400`  |

When implementing any section, reference the corresponding node ID above.
If the Figma MCP is connected in Cursor, you can call it with:
`get_design_context(nodeId: "5:334")` to pull the exact code spec.

---

## WHAT TO NEVER DO

- Never use hardcoded hex colors — always use Tailwind token classes
- Never use plain `<img>` — always `next/image`
- Never write inline styles unless absolutely unavoidable
- Never create a new component for something that already exists in `src/components/ui/`
- Never skip `alt` text on images
- Never call analytics platforms directly — use `trackEvent()`
- Never use `px-` values that break the 8px spacing grid
- Never write CSS outside of Tailwind utilities (no custom CSS files except `globals.css`)
- Never add new npm packages without asking first

---

## WHAT TO ALWAYS DO

- Always write mobile-first (base styles = mobile, then `md:` / `lg:` for desktop)
- Always use TypeScript interfaces for component props
- Always use `next/image` with explicit `width` and `height` or `fill`
- Always use semantic HTML elements
- Always run `trackEvent()` on key interactions
- Always match the Figma design — if unsure, ask for the node ID and pull the spec
- Always keep components under ~150 lines — split into sub-components if larger
- Always export a `metadata` object from each page file
